{"title_page": "Boys' School", "text_new": "{{Infobox film\n| name           = Boys' School\n| image          = Boys School Christian-Jaque.jpg\n| image_size     = \n| caption        = \n| director       = [[Christian-Jaque]]\n| producer       = \n| writer         =\n| starring       = [[Erich von Stroheim]]<br>[[Michel Simon]]<br>[[Robert Le Vigan]]<br>[[Marcel Mouloudji]]\n| music          = Henry Verdun\n| cinematography = Marcel Lusien\n| editing        = \n| studio         = Dimeco Productions\n| distributor    = Les Films Vog (France)<br>[[Columbia Pictures]] (USA)\n| released       = {{Film date|1938|04|06|France|1939|06|05|USA}}\n| runtime        = 98 minutes\n| country        = France\n| language       = French\n| budget         = \n}}\n'''''Boys' School''''' (''Les Disparus de Saint-Agil'' in French) is a 1938 French drama film by [[Christian-Jaque]] based on the novel of the same title by [[Pierre V\u00e9ry]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://en.unifrance.org/movie/2121/boys-school|title=Boys' School|publisher=unifrance.org |accessdate=2014-02-21}}</ref> It has become a [[cult film]]. <ref>{{cite web|author=filmsdefrance.com |url=http://www.filmsdefrance.com/review/les-disparus-de-saint-agil-1938.html |title=Les Disparus de Saint-Agil (1938) \u2013 Christian-Jaque \u2013 film review |publisher=Filmsdefrance.com |date= |accessdate=2015-12-17}}</ref>\n\n==Plot==\nShortly before the war, strange things happen at night at the School of Saint-Agil. Students begin to disappear... Three students of Saint-Agil, Beaume Sorgue and Macroy, have created a secret society to prepare leaving for America. One evening, one of them, Sorgue, sees a man through a wall in the natural sciences class. He then disappears after having been sent to the principal's office. When Macroy vanishes in turn, the whole institution is in turmoil. The last member of the secret society still at school, Beaume, might be expelled as well after the yearly school party. During this party, Lemel, the alcoholic art teacher, dies after a fall when a power outage leaves the school in the black. Everyone believes in an accident but Beaume decides to investigate. He chooses to disappear as well and, with the help of the mysterious and spooky English teacher, he manages to discover the counterfeiting business at work in the school insides.\n\n==Cast==\n* [[Marcel Mouloudji]] as Philippe Macroy\n* [[Jean Claudio]] as Mathieu Sorgue\n* [[Erich von Stroheim]] as Walter, the English teacher\n* [[Michel Simon]] as Lemel, the art teacher\n* [[Robert Le Vigan]] as C\u00e9sar, the counterfeiter\n* [[Armand Bernard]] as Mazeau, the concierge\n* [[Aim\u00e9 Clariond]] as the school principal\n* [[Ren\u00e9 G\u00e9nin]] as Donnadieu, the music teacher\n* [[Serge Reggiani]] as a schoolboy\n* [[Charles Aznavour]] as a schoolboy\n* [[Robert Rollis]] as a schoolboy\n* Serge Grave as Beaume\n* Jacques Derives as Planet\n* Martial R\u00e8be as the dorm supervisor\n* [[Pierre Labry]] as Bernardin\n* Albert Malbert as Alexis, the miller\n* F\u00e9lix Claude as a schoolboy\n* Jean Buquet as the snitch\n* Claude Roy as the schoolboy with a turtle\n* Robert Ozanne as a nurse\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb title|30062}}\n{{Christian-Jaque}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Boys' School}}\n[[Category:1930s drama films]]\n[[Category:1938 films]]\n[[Category:French black-and-white films]]\n[[Category:Films directed by Christian-Jaque]]\n[[Category:Films set in France]]\n[[Category:French films]]\n[[Category:Films based on works by Pierre V\u00e9ry]]\n[[Category:Boarding school films]]\n[[Category:Columbia Pictures films]]\n[[Category:French drama films]]\n{{1930s-France-film-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox film\n| name           = Boys' School\n| image          = Boys School Christian-Jaque.jpg\n| image_size     = \n| caption        = \n| director       = [[Christian-Jaque]]\n| producer       = \n| writer         =\n| starring       = [[Erich von Stroheim]]<br>[[Michel Simon]]<br>[[Robert Le Vigan]]<br>[[Marcel Mouloudji]]\n| music          = Henry Verdun\n| cinematography = Marcel Lusien\n| editing        = \n| studio         = Dimeco Productions\n| distributor    = Les Films Vog (France)<br>[[Columbia Pictures]] (USA)\n| released       = {{Film date|1938|04|06|France|1939|06|05|USA}}\n| runtime        = 98 minutes\n| country        = France\n| language       = French\n| budget         = \n}}\n'''''Boys' School''''' (''Les Disparus de Saint-Agil'' in French) is a 1938 French drama film by [[Christian-Jaque]] based on the novel of the same title by [[Pierre V\u00e9ry]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://en.unifrance.org/movie/2121/boys-school|title=Boys' School|publisher=unifrance.org |accessdate=2014-02-21}}</ref> It has become a [[cult movie]]. <ref>{{cite web|author=filmsdefrance.com |url=http://www.filmsdefrance.com/review/les-disparus-de-saint-agil-1938.html |title=Les Disparus de Saint-Agil (1938) \u2013 Christian-Jaque \u2013 film review |publisher=Filmsdefrance.com |date= |accessdate=2015-12-17}}</ref>\n\n==Plot==\nShortly before the war, strange things happen at night at the School of Saint-Agil. Students begin to disappear... Three students of Saint-Agil, Beaume Sorgue and Macroy, have created a secret society to prepare leaving for America. One evening, one of them, Sorgue, sees a man through a wall in the natural sciences class. He then disappears after having been sent to the principal's office. When Macroy vanishes in turn, the whole institution is in turmoil. The last member of the secret society still at school, Beaume, might be expelled as well after the yearly school party. During this party, Lemel, the alcoholic art teacher, dies after a fall when a power outage leaves the school in the black. Everyone believes in an accident but Beaume decides to investigate. He chooses to disappear as well and, with the help of the mysterious and spooky English teacher, he manages to discover the counterfeiting business at work in the school insides.\n\n==Cast==\n* [[Marcel Mouloudji]] as Philippe Macroy\n* [[Jean Claudio]] as Mathieu Sorgue\n* [[Erich von Stroheim]] as Walter, the English teacher\n* [[Michel Simon]] as Lemel, the art teacher\n* [[Robert Le Vigan]] as C\u00e9sar, the counterfeiter\n* [[Armand Bernard]] as Mazeau, the concierge\n* [[Aim\u00e9 Clariond]] as the school principal\n* [[Ren\u00e9 G\u00e9nin]] as Donnadieu, the music teacher\n* [[Serge Reggiani]] as a schoolboy\n* [[Charles Aznavour]] as a schoolboy\n* [[Robert Rollis]] as a schoolboy\n* Serge Grave as Beaume\n* Jacques Derives as Planet\n* Martial R\u00e8be as the dorm supervisor\n* [[Pierre Labry]] as Bernardin\n* Albert Malbert as Alexis, the miller\n* F\u00e9lix Claude as a schoolboy\n* Jean Buquet as the snitch\n* Claude Roy as the schoolboy with a turtle\n* Robert Ozanne as a nurse\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb title|30062}}\n{{Christian-Jaque}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Boys' School}}\n[[Category:1930s drama films]]\n[[Category:1938 films]]\n[[Category:French black-and-white films]]\n[[Category:Films directed by Christian-Jaque]]\n[[Category:Films set in France]]\n[[Category:French films]]\n[[Category:Films based on works by Pierre V\u00e9ry]]\n[[Category:Boarding school films]]\n[[Category:Columbia Pictures films]]\n[[Category:French drama films]]\n{{1930s-France-film-stub}}\n", "name_user": "TMProofreader", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Boys%27_School"}
